	<title>Examples of Multiplying a Matrix by a Number</title>
	<caption>Multiplying a Matrix by a Number</caption>
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>The (scalar) product of the matrix</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					{\color{blue}A}\ =\ 
					\left[\begin{array}{rrr}
					{\color{blue}4} & {\color{blue}-2} & {\color{blue}0} \\
					{\color{blue}6} & {\color{blue}0} & {\color{blue}-4}
					\end{array}\right]
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>by the number <latex>t={\color{red}3}</latex> is</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\aligned
					{\color{red}3}\cdot {\color{blue}A} \ &=\ 
					{\color{red}3}\cdot
					\left[\begin{array}{rrr}
					{\color{blue}4} & {\color{blue}-2} & {\color{blue}0} \\
					{\color{blue}6} & {\color{blue}0} & {\color{blue}-4}
					\end{array}\right] \\
					&=\ \left[\begin{array}{rrr}
					{\color{red}3}\cdot{\color{blue}4} & {\color{red}3}\cdot({\color{blue}-2}) & {\color{red}3}\cdot{\color{blue}0} \\
					{\color{red}3}\cdot{\color{blue}6} & {\color{red}3}\cdot{\color{blue}0} & {\color{red}3}\cdot{\color{blue}-4}
					\end{array}\right] \\
					&=\ 
					\left[\begin{array}{rrr}
					12 & -6 & 0 \\
					18 & 0 & -12
					\end{array}\right] \\
					\endaligned
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</statement>
	</showme>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>In general, the product of a matrix <latex>{\color{blue}A}</latex> of size <latex>(m,n)</latex> by a number <latex>{\color{red}t}</latex> with</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					{\color{blue}A}\ =\ 
					\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
					{\color{blue}a_{11}} & \cdots & {\color{blue}a_{1n}} \\
					\vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
					{\color{blue}a_{m1}} & \cdots & {\color{blue}a_{mn}}
					\end{array}\right]
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>is</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\aligned
					{\color{red}t}\cdot {\color{blue}A} &=\ 
					{\color{red}t}\cdot \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
					{\color{blue}a_{11}} & \cdots & {\color{blue}a_{1n}} \\
					\vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
					{\color{blue}a_{m1}} & \cdots & {\color{blue}a_{mn}}
					\end{array}\right] \\
					&=\ 
					\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
					{\color{red}t}\cdot {\color{blue}a_{11}} & \cdots & {\color{red}t}\cdot {\color{blue}a_{1n}} \\
					\vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
					{\color{red}t}\cdot {\color{blue}a_{m1}} & \cdots & {\color{red}t}\cdot {\color{blue}a_{mn}}
					\end{array}\right]
					\endaligned
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</statement>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>